This paper discusses the design and implementation of a high-concurrency re=
al-time data processing architecture for a cross-border eCommerce platform.=
 To address the massive order streams, user behavior logs, and real-time ri=
sk control requirements during major sales events, this project adopted a L=
ambda-based big data architecture. By implementing Flink CDC for non-intrus=
ive data ingestion, leveraging Flink's state management and Async I/O to re=
solve multi-source data enrichment latency, and utilizing Kafka's buffering=
 capabilities to manage system backpressure, the architecture successfully =
reduced end-to-end latency from minutes to under 200ms. It supported a peak=
 of 300,000 TPS during the "Double 11" shopping festival, ensuring high ava=
ilability and data consistency.</p><hr data-path-to-node=3D"7"><h4 data-pat=
