In 2025, I led the upgrade of the "Real-time Data Mid-platform" for a leadi=
ng cross-border eCommerce platform. As the company's global business expand=
ed, the legacy Hive-based batch processing architecture became inadequate. =
During major promotions like "Double 11," the platform faced severe challen=
ges: first, <b data-path-to-node=3D"10" data-index-in-node=3D"321">lack of =
timeliness</b>, as marketing teams required per-second GMV dashboards while=
 the old system had a 2-hour lag; second, <b data-path-to-node=3D"10" data-=
index-in-node=3D"442">stability risks</b>, where instantaneous traffic spik=
es often led to database connection pool overflows; and third, <b data-path=
-to-node=3D"10" data-index-in-node=3D"554">data silos</b>, where order, pro=
duct, and user info were scattered across databases, resulting in poor real=
-time join performance. As the system architect, I decided to refactor the =
data pipeline and build a resilient, real-time responsive Lambda architectu=
re.</p><hr data-path-to-node=3D"11"><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"12">=F0=9F=9B=
